{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Raphaela - The female version of Gabriel both belonging in tower class, Raphaela was released as a BP unit. Her kit seemed pretty underwhelming at first outside of the 2% MDL, but the 2% MDL alone made her basically impossible to kill for 3 cost and just her addition to the game increased the average length of P","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"VP matches by 10%. As a result, her MDL was soon nerfed to 4%.

","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"After in game tests, it quickly revealed her strength that was not mentioned in her kit. Her tower mode has an absurd hit-stun and with the 4m pseudo forward deployment, she can completely prevent units with slow attack speed from performing any action. Also, her skill multipliers are pretty insane and combined with her massive ATK% self-buffs and DPS gears, she can actually nuke backline units with both her special skill and her 50% pre-charged ult, while still applying pretty strong buffs/debuffs.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"As for PVE, she has some uses, but requires manual play or else she just sits at the back for 15 seconds.

